caption: OK guys: Can you tell a difference between the AirPods Pro 1 and the AirPods Pro 3 in terms of microphone quality. I filmed this on an iPhone 14 Pro btw...
transcript: Hey, it's Jason Murzbaum of St. Louis Public Radio. I have not seen a lot of coverage about how the microphones on the new AirPods Pro 3s compared to older models. Um, for a lot of people like me who use their phones to make videos, um, we typically just haven't used AirPods as a, a de facto microphone. Right now, I am actually talking into the AirPods Pro One. I bought these probably about four years ago and I'm going to do a comparison of this with the AirPods Pro 3s which arrived in the mail today, September 19th, 2025. Okay, so right now, I have the AirPod Pro 3s in my ear. First of all, the the noise cancellation on this, substantially better than the AirPod Pro One. Um, I'm pretty sure that the noise cancellation was better with the AirPod Pros too, but like it's a night and day difference. It is honestly, kind of, kind of eerie about like how much it blocks out all the noise. Um, it also fits really well in the ear. I know Apple had been talking a lot about how they changed the way that like these AirPods go into the ear canal. Um, I, I'm not a person that really struggled with the other AirPods, but um, the this fits really nicely. So, I'm going to be really interested to hear the sound quality on this, because again, there's been a lot of talk about how music sounds and how this has a heart rate monitor in it and how it is like designed a little bit differently. But again, if you're someone like me, and you use your iPhone a lot to create social media videos, this is the, this is the old AirPods. You just don't really use these if you have other alternatives and it would be interesting if these are good sound quality to have another option. I'm not, I don't know if I would use these all the time even if the sound quality was good. Um, I do kind of like having either like an actual microphone with the St. Louis Public Radio logo on it or the the DGIs just because I just like them, but this could be a good way to make a video in a pinch. So, I'm looking forward to hearing the difference.

caption:
AirPods Pro 3 introduces a set of breakthrough features, including real-time live translation, new fitness sensors, re-engineered sound hardware, much longer battery life, and refined comfort and accessibility options.

Live Translation and Multilingual Communication
Live Translation allows seamless, real-time conversations across languages using on-device Apple Intelligence.

Users can trigger translation mode with a gesture on the AirPods, automatically lowering background noise, then hear translated speech directly in their ears.

If both participants wear compatible AirPods, each hears translations in their own language; if only one does, live transcriptions appear on the paired iPhone for the other person.

At launch, languages include English, French, German, Portuguese (Brazil), and Spanish (Spain), with Italian, Japanese, Korean, and Chinese (simplified) coming later in 2025.
